## Fractional CFO Cost vs. Full-Time CFO Salary

The real comparison must include **total cost of ownership**, not just base pay.

| Cost Component | Fractional CFO | Full-Time CFO |
|----------------|----------------|----------------|
| Monthly Cost | $3K‚Äì$12K | $15K‚Äì$25K+ |
| Annual Cost | $36K‚Äì$180K | $250K‚Äì$400K |
| Benefits & Taxes | Included | +25‚Äì35% overhead |
| Infrastructure | Included | Office, software, admin |
| Hiring Risk | None | 30‚Äì40% failure rate |
| Flexibility | Scalable | Fixed commitment |

Fractional CFOs deliver **executive-level expertise** for a fraction of the cost‚Äîwith greater agility and lower risk.

---

## Hidden Costs of a Full-Time CFO

- **Recruitment:** 25‚Äì30% of first-year salary  
- **Onboarding delay:** 3‚Äì6 months before productivity  
- **Turnover risk:** 30‚Äì40% of hires fail within 18 months  

A $250K hire often costs **$315K‚Äì$340K** after taxes and benefits‚Äîbefore office overhead.

